 <h2>Online Help for OUTSTANDING STATEMENT Object</h2>
  
<br></br><br></br>
This is an Object to create and export report  to PDF or excel template.<br></br>
There are two types of report in this object.<br></br>
<ul>
1.CUSTOMER INVOICE SUMMARY REPORT<br></br> 
(Account whose Account type is Customer is in invoice-to, shows the receivable)<br></br>
2.PARTNER OUTSTANDING STATEMENT REPORT<br></br>
(Account whose Account type is Partner and either in Invoice-To or Payment-To.)
</ul>
If the partner is in Invoice-To, it will show in the Debit List. If the patner is in Payment-to, it will show in the Credit List.
<br></br>
<br></br>
<h1>To utilize</h1><br></br> 
<ul>
1.Choose the type of report (CUSTOMER INVOICE SUMMARY REPORT/PARTNER OUTSTANDING STATEMENT REPORT)<br></br>  
2.Choose the Language of the report.<br></br>
3.Determine the start date and end date for the certain period which report will be generated.<br></br>
4.Press “Generate Report” and you will see the shipments, subtotal of the shipments, total balance of the Customers who has receivable remaining or the unsettled balance of DEBIT/CREDIT of partners for that period.<br></br>
5.Press Excel or PDF and you can issue report in Excel file or PDF file.<br></br>
</ul>
<br></br>
<h1>### For CUSTOMER INVOICE SUMMARY REPORT</h1><br></br>
“PDF Total” or “EXCEL Total” shows the total of PAYENT EXCLUDE TAX and ADVANCE PAYMENT.<br></br>
“PDF PAYENT EXCLUDE TAX” or “Excel PAYENT EXCLUDE TAX” shows amount exclude the ADVANCE PAYMENT.<br></br>
“PDF ADVANCE PAYMENT” or “EXCEL ADVANCED PAYMENT” shows amount of ADVANCE PAYMENT only.<br></br>
To distinguish ADVANCE PAYMENT from PAYMENT EXCLUDE TAX, stick the box of DUTY SELLING FOR ADVANCE PAYMENT  in HB/L Selling/Buying.<br></br>
 Also, to show report properly,<br></br> 
<ul> 
1.Status should be before “Invoice Issued” <br></br>
2. UNPAID BALANCE OF SELLING(LOCAL) must not be 0.   <br></br>
3. Record type must not be “Locked”.<br></br>
</ul>
